tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mildly elevated total and LDL cholesterol, suggesting increased cardiovascular risk. There is evidence of mild normocytic, normochromic anemia (low RBC, hemoglobin, and hematocrit) with normal indices, which may warrant further evaluation. Other parameters, including leukocytes and platelets, are within normal limits. Clinical correlation and follow-up are recommended.
